title: Canada warns LGBTQ travelers to be cautious of U.S. laws
description: Canada is advising LGBTQ travelers planning trips to the United States to check how they might be affected by recently passed laws in some states, Ottawa said on Tuesday.

title: Guatemala progressive candidate confirmed as presidential winner, but his party is suspended
description: Progressive candidate Bernardo Arévalo was confirmed as the winner of Guatemala’s presidential election but a government body ordered his political party suspended.

title: Memorial service for Wagner chief Prigozhin held, his spokespeople say
description: A memorial service has taken place for mercenary chief Yevgeny Prigozhin, who was killed in a plane crash last week, his spokespeople said Tuesday.

title: Funeral held for a deputy of Wagner group's Yevgeny Prigozhin
description: A funeral was held in St. Petersburg, Russia, understood to be for the Wagner mercenary group's logistics chief Valery Chekalov, who died in the Aug. 23 airplane crash alongside its leader Yevgeny Prigozhin.

title: Russian mercenaries bid farewell to Prigozhin’s logistics chief at funeral
description: Russian mercenaries gathered on Tuesday for the funeral of one of Yevgeny Prigozhin’s deputies who was killed with his boss in a plane crash last week, though the Kremlin said President Vladimir Putin had no plans to attend Prigozhin’s funeral.

title: North Korea's Kim Jong Un marks Navy Day with his daughter
description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un visited his navy headquarters, with state media reports highlighting Kim's daughter, and the country's nuclear preparedness.

title: More than 60 people arrested at a gay wedding in southern Nigeria
description: Police in Nigeria said they detained at least 67 people celebrating a gay wedding, in one of the country’s largest arrests targeting outlawed homosexuality.

title: Afghans who fought in secret CIA-trained force face legal uncertainty in the U.S.
description: Afghans who fought under the CIA's command for years say they now face a legal limbo in the U.S. and are asking Congress and the Biden administration for help.

title: Live worm plucked from woman’s brain in Australia, a world first
description: A woman who was admitted to hospital with mystery symptoms in Australia had a live, parasitic worm plucked from her brain.

title: Crank calls and stone throwing: Chinese harassment hits Japan over Fukushima water release
description: China and Japan have traded accusations of harassment, including nuisance phone calls, amid a dispute over the release of water from the Fukushima nuclear plant.

title: Surgeon extracts live worm from patient's brain
description: A neurosurgeon investigating a woman’s mystery symptoms in an Australian hospital says she plucked a wriggling worm from the patient’s brain.

title: Residents of beautiful Austrian town block tunnel in protest over tourism
description: Residents of the Austrian lakeside town of Hallstatt demonstrated against mass tourism by blocking a tunnel leading to the town on Sunday.

title: Is the bride 25 or younger? Couples get cash reward to promote earlier marriage in China
description: Local Chinese officials trying to encourage earlier marriages are offering young couples a cash reward if they get married while the bride is 25 or younger.

title: Kim Jong Un says nuclear weapons to be deployed to North Korea's navy
description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un said his country's navy would become “a component of the state nuclear deterrence,” state media said Tuesday, as the U.S., South Korea and Japan held a trilateral naval exercise to deal with North Korea’s evolving nuclear threats.

title: U.S. Marines killed in Australian Osprey crash are identified
description: Three U.S. Marines killed in the weekend crash of an Osprey aircraft in Australia were identified Monday.

title: Spanish soccer chief under investigation over kiss
description: Outrage continues to grow, along with calls for the resignation of Luis Rubiales, after he kissed a female soccer player on the lips during a celebration of Spain’s victory in the World Cup. NBC’s Molly Hunter explains.
